<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">Aye soup, ye have a good idea. Asking for mana in return is a very fair payment for a SoW. And I agree warriors are a gray area, but no mind, us honorable Shaman always find a solution :)<p>

Seasons 9-15 did come with much sow begging. Aye, they are begging, not asking, if coin is not offered in return for your SoWing. And as an Barbarian, I have very little patience for begging filth.<p>

I offer no solution to the SoW problem, I just lived with all of the requests for SoWs. Moving to Oasis helped, but moving to Rathe helped even more. It seems that the older folks are less concerned with SoW, which is nice for us Shamans and the druids of Norrath. Elders are good people in my book.<p>

OOC: I have also brought up 4 non-sowing/non-binding characters past 20, and I never *had* to have a SoW. I never begged for one either. SoW may have saved my life a few times, but I would have had to be SoWed constantly for those few life-savers (and who wants to sow all characters constantly, lol.) In other words, SoW is a want, not a need.<p>

Binding *is* a need. I bind anybody who needs one, and I have never been compensated for it. In my other lives, I could *always* get somewhere without a Sow. But I could never bind myself to a city without a binding caster. And sometimes it would take me over an hour to get a bind...a long, boring hour. - OOC<p>

Alright all ye in Norrath, 'tis my 2cp worth. Bind generously, but only SoW for donations or random acts of kindness. Do not SoW filthy beggars. Be safe all and hunt honorably.<p>

Aenaan<br>
Barbarian Shaman<br>
20th Season<p>

Veeshan</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
