<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">Hail Brother,<p>

As a shaman in the 15th season, I find myself inundated with requests and demands to SoW. Requests I gladly fill, proved they are for specific reasons, such as CR, meeting group, hooking up a guild brother or what have you. Binding I do free of charge as well, as I run several non casting classes and I agree on the wait as well.<p>

What I will NOT do anymore is buff, heal, sow or otherwise aid begging, rude palyers. Example--&gt; Last night, in FP, while medding from combat in N Ro., and just before I logged, mind you, I received a bonk on me head. Then the demand "Bind ME". No tell, no request, no hail, just an assault and demand. Now, as an elder warrior, I take personal affront to a younger player's behavior like this. Yet I resisted the temptation to act as a child and simply responded with this ---&gt; "We northmen respect courtesy and integrity, not demands.". For this I got the finger.<p>

My point is simple, I agree with ye brother. Not only do I not help beggards, but I use the above reply when demands are laid upon me.<p>

If ye see me in FP, send me a tell Aenaan. <p>

Peace<p>

Wordaen<br>
Barbarian Shaman<br>
15th Circle of Power<br>
Elite Force</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
