<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">I spent the better part of an hour last evening attempting to run from Qeynos to EK.  Why so long you ask?<p>

Well....  Run 5 steps, SOW a beggar, heal a beggar, SOW a beggar, buff a beggar.  Med....  etc.  I'll never make level 20 at this rate.  hehe<p>

I like to do good deeds when I can.  And SOW.... I do them. MOST of the time.  But at times it hurts.  <p>

Picture this. I was even in a group once, camping Broon in EK.  Three of us all under 20th.  A tough match with Broon indeed.  So I use ALL of my mana each fight and have to full med in the 5 minutes before Broon appears again.  One fight, an outsider intervenes in our struggle with Broon uninvited and nearly steals the kill from us.  Then has the nerve to ask for a SOW.  I'm getting P.O.'ed so I say NO.  One of my groupmates has the nerve to ORDER ME to give this interloper a SOW and burn precious mana that I know I will need in less than 2 minutes....   I said NO again, to both of them and left the group.  <p>

I particularly distain the beggars who demand a SOW from you and wait.  Then poke you and wait.  Then ask again and wait.  Then when you tell them NO to SOW, they make a comment like this;  "Ok, I guess I'll keep my 2PP then."   hehehe.   2PP that was NOT offered in the first place is easy to take back.   hehehe.<p>

I agree 100% with Grohm.  NEVER feel guilty about saying no to SOWing beggars.  And NEVER give in to blackmail for it.  <p>

BTW, I have am in the procees of testing a new philosophy;  That I will only SOW for free when I have 100% mana. So if a beggar politely asks for a SOW while I am medding I tell them that I will provide them with a SOW if they will wait until I am at 100% mana (about 4-5 minutes).  This discourages some of those who don't REALLY NEED a SOW.<hr>Chastan Winterlyn</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
