<td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="5" cellpadding="5" align="CENTER">
<tr>
<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">Hail fellow shamans,<br>
   I am currently a barbarian shaman of the 21st season (2 bubs from 22) and I have found a very good way to make quite a profit from SoW and other buffs we possess.  When I enter a new zone and I do not know many of the characters there, I announce my presence as a shaman of the 21st rank.  Then I /shout "free SoW's for the next five minutes at ____ location" I find that this lets everyone know that I am a generous guy.  Most people do not pay for the SoW's (since I did say free), but the is always the occasional high level char who feels the need to give ample payment to me for all the free SoW's I gave out.  I have received anywhere from 1 platinum to 150 platinum for a "free sow".  After the time is up I simply /shout "Free SoW's up in 30 seconds, better hurry!!!" Most people come in the last few seconds just because they had to run a long way for their SoW.  When I am known in a zone, which now I am renowned in the Karanas and Everfrost, I just /ooc "Hello everone, I'm back" and I get a lot of friends who I have grouped with or SoW'ed for free saying hello then telling me that they need SoW and will be more than glad to pay for it.  When I SoW for "donations" I do not expect anything more than 2pp, but often receive upwards of 50pp, If a char is level 10 or lower I do not except more than 5 gold unless it is a twinked char.  If a char is level 1-5 I will completely buff them for free (level 19 buffs can level a little guy extremely fast, ex. raising a warrior strength by 20).  I don't mind SoWing a beggar simply because at level 21 it costs almost no mana to cast SoW and is a simple 3 second med to get the mana back.  The best thing to do before giving free SoW's is to /shout "Trading SoW for Breeze or Clarity at _____", clarity takes my oom to fm time from around 3 minutes to around 1 minute and thus even a low level can SoW tons of people and still keep his mana up.<p>

     Just my 2cp's worth on the subject of Sowing,<p>

                       Darkfenix Shadowstalker</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
